Text: RE ColoradoThanks tell me whenever it is convinant for you Original Message From Giron Darron C Sent Tuesday October AM To Logan III Jackson Subject RE Colorado I remembered to bring them Maybe we can get together later today DG Original Message From Logan III Jackson Sent Monday October PM To Giron Darron C Subject RE Colorado Are yall in the new building If so I will come over and check it out Thanks Again JDLIII Original Message From Giron Darron C Sent Monday October AM To Logan III Jackson Subject RE Colorado Sold I also have two End Zone passes also Ill bring them up here tomorrow DG Original Message From Logan III Jackson Sent Friday October AM To Giron Darron C Subject RE Colorado Thanks alot I would love to use them if at all possible So for the late response I was out of the office yesterday Original Message From Giron Darron C Sent Thursday October PM To Logan III Jackson Subject Colorado We decided last night not to go to the Colorado game next week Ive got two at face if youre interested Tough one last weekend It sure sucks that OU got that good that fast Im out tomorrow back on Monday See ya DG

FW OU Stadium RenovationHOOKEM Original Message From ENRON Sent Tuesday November PM To DCPcom Brian IMFUNDSCOM Subject OU Stadium Renovation Norman AP Oklahoma University Athletic Director Joe Castiglione announced today that due to recent developments the renovations at Owen Field are well ahead of schedule and will come in under costs Seems over fans shit a brick during the fourth quarter of the bedlam football game providing the necessary materials to begin work right away The information transmitted is intended only for the person or entity to which it is addressed and may contain confidential andor privileged material Any review retransmission dissemination or other use of or taking of any action in reliance upon this information by persons or entities other than the intended recipient is prohibited If you received this in error please contact the sender and delete the material from any computer

FW If men designed brasPST Original Message From Jordan Arriaga orthMarqcomENRON Sent Wednesday January PM To Alison Moore Andy Armand Brian Brian Burden Email Carey Ford catherine Dwayne Grace Ellen Logan III Jackson Kerry Lacey Lauri MacKenna Michele Mary Worth Robyn Simonton Sarah ObexerFields Subject If men designed bras IfMenDesignedBrasjpg IfMenDesignedBrasjpg

Fwd FW Aggies Demand a RecountForwarded by Jackson LoganHOUECT on AM Tara Talbot on AM To Danielle IMFUNDScom MeredithO IMFUNDScom ZLQScom ZLQScom RonnyeE SAconococom cc Subject Fwd FW Aggies Demand a Recount Ellyn Haikin AM Subject FW Aggies Demand a Recount College Station TX AP RC Slocum and the Texas AM Aggies are demanding a recount of the game in which Oklahoma won to The end zones were confusing says Slocum Im sure that some of the touchdowns that went in Oklahomas end zone were meant to go into ours We were scoring in those end zones also Oklahoma would never have scored thirtyfive points Theres no way we lost this one AM demands a recount Oklahoma officials are calling this outrageous They agreed to the size shape and locations of the end zones prior to kickoff replies OU coach Bob Stoops If they had a problem with them they should have said so before we started You dont get to keep playing until youre happy with the outcome Someone had to lose Weve scored over thirtyfive points many times AM has sent lawyers farmers and those guys in the funny boots as well as that damn dog down to Kyle Field where the scoreboard will be tested We are confident that when the points are retotaled we will be the winner of the game says Slocum OU also points out that in many games prior to this one the same end zones were used They didnt have a problem with the end zones until they lost says Stoops Outside of Kyle Field AM student protesters have gathered outside bearing signs such as AM wants a fair game WHOOOOOOP Students thoughts echoed their signs All we want is a fair total of the points before we declare a winner says student Karen Hays an aggie from Marfa We need to proceed cautiously and not rush to judgment before we declare a winner ABC around pm central time had mistakenly declared AM the winner despite the slim point lead the Aggies held at that point At about pm with the game still to close to call ABC had to back off its prediction College football analyst Brent Musburger made the call We felt that with a number of points still not added in by Jamaar Tombs and the Aggies we were certain AM would carry this game We may have been premature in our prediction William G Lowerre Schweinle Parish Lowerre PC Fannin Suite Houston TX fax
